ence\": \"Over 1,000 medals were handed out at the Paris Olympics, which included 329 events across 32 sports.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 382, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Over 1,000 medals\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 299}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 337}, {\"ngram\": \"329 events\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 364}, {\"ngram\": \"32 sports\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 381}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USA and China both claimed 40 gold medals, with Japan clinching 20.\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 384, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999201331807, \"rank\": 5.11660882738033e-08, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9996218404016698, \"rank\": 0.00028571761283255673, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9834562494333804, \"rank\": 0.01593737321976742, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"40 gold medals\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USA won the most medals in total after also bagging 44 silvers and 42 bronzes.\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"USA\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"the most medals\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 484}, {\"ngram\": \"44 silvers\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 514}, {\"ngram\": \"42 bronzes\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According toThe Times, signs of deterioration began to appear just days after athletes had received their medals.\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 645, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"toThe Times\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"signs\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 560}, {\"ngram\": \"deterioration\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"their medals\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 644}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And more than 100 winners have since returned their shiny prizes.\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than 100 winners\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 671}, {\"ngram\": \"their shiny prizes\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 710}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Faulty varnish has been blamed for the issues, with bronze medals affected more than the golds and silvers.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Faulty varnish\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"the issues\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze medals\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"the golds\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"silvers\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 819}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze medals are mainly made from copper but include a small amount of zinc and tin.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bronze medals\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 838}, {\"ngram\": \"copper\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 866}, {\"ngram\": \"a small amount\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 893}, {\"ngram\": \"zinc\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"tin\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the damage appears to have occurred after the mint opted to use an anti-corrosion varnish to comply with EU regulations when the usage of the toxic chromium trioxide was banned.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999999825008673, \"rank\": 9.131330242176284e-09, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the damage\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"the mint\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"an anti-corrosion varnish\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"the usage\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"the toxic chromium trioxide\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1081}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French mint plans to replace the medals and are working with Paris 2024 chiefs to assess claims and understand the reasons behind the damage.\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9702478447261726, \"rank\": 0.025709485732011275, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1160, \"end\": 1170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5922737190470803e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"chiefs\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1177}, {\"ngram\": \"claims\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"the reasons\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"the damage\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Caitlin Clark says she was thankful after missing out on the Olympics Some competitors have taken to social media to air their grievances over the state of the medals, with French swimmer Clement Se